  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Lay</strong> the cucumber flat on your chopping board and use a rolling pin to bash it so that it splits and breaks up</p>\r\n<p>Tip: Wear an apron and lay a tea towel over the cucumber as the juices splatter!</p>\r\n<p><strong>Cut</strong> the broken cucumber into rough, bite-size pieces</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/466.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/466.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/466.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/466.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/466.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Boil</strong> a kettle (used in step 3)</p>\r\n<p><strong>Peel</strong> and chop (or grate) the garlic very finely</p>\r\n<p><strong>Peel</strong> the ginger (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and chop (or grate) it very finely</p>\r\n<p><strong>Mix</strong> the cucumber, garlic, ginger, chilli flakes (can't handle the heat? Go easy!), a pinch of sugar and 2 tsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> (3 tsp)</span> salt in sieve over a bowl</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/466.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/466.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/466.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/466.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/466.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Meanwhile</strong>, break the noodles in half and add them to a pot of boiled salted water on a high heat</p>\r\n<p><strong>When</strong> boiling, reduce the heat to low and cook for 6-8 min or until cooked through with a slight bite, loosening with a fork</p>\r\n<p><strong>Once</strong> cooked, drain them under cold water and set aside</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/466.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/466.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
